Name: King of French Fries
Desc: A new fried fast food brand that sells cheap, fast, convenient foods.\nDon't try the milk shakes here! — An anonymous tourist

Name: Pulao Snacks
Desc: A stall selling traditional Kowloong food, with a sign featuring an arrogant portrait of its owner.\n"I didn't mean to make it that way!" —Pulao

Name: Seafood Fried Rice
Desc: Freshly done seafood fried rice! You get to pick the cook! Mr. Yellow is an expert. Mr. Blue works hard. And Mr. Pink is cute! — An anonymous redhead girl

Name: Fresh Apple Juice
Desc: A drink shop that sells apple juice with unique flavors.\nYawn... An apple a day keeps the nightmare away. — A Construct that borrows your shoulder as the pillow

Name: Squeezed Lemon Juice
Desc: A drink shop that sells lemon juice with special flavors.\nIt's so sour! One more lick. So sour! One more lick again. So sour! — A tourist with a crunched-up face

Name: Berry Juice
Desc: A drink shop that sells blueberry juice with special flavors.

Name: Ice Cream Store
Desc: A shop that sells all kinds of ice creams. There's always a long line in front of it during the hot weather.

Name: Peach Juice
Desc: A cold drink shop that sells fresh juice. Popular among young tourists.

Name: Special Dessert
Desc: A mobile dessert stall with desserts of various flavors.\nDoes it fulfill all your expectations of desserts? — The dessert stall owner

Name: Dynamic Paintings Exhibition Area
Desc: Mainly exhibits Constructs' bravery in battle. It's said that one could hear the sounds of battle upon seeing the paintings.\nThe prison of the fate! — Hallucination from nowhere

Name: Classical Paintings Exhibition Area
Desc: Mainly exhibits classic Kowloong paintings. Full of mystery and elegance.\nThis one is definitely real. I inherited it from Grandpa. — An excited passer-by

Name: Cartoon Paintings Exhibition Area
Desc: Cartoon paintings of various styles are on exhibition here. The first 20 buyers will receive a free autograph of the painter.\nHow is it? Did they buy any of my paintings? — An anonymous pink-haired girl

Name: Passion Statue
Desc: Seems to be some popular pink shark mascot. Most statues depict it in the act of working hard.

Name: Cute Statue
Desc: Seems to be some popular yellow shark mascot. It's cute, anyway.

Name: Classic Statue
Desc: A classic blue shark mascot who still has a lot of fans to this day.

Name: Boxing Champion
Desc: A classic fighting game that has 12 playable characters.\nYou go first. I'll let you have five punches. — Yata

Name: City of Evil Souls
Desc: A classic side-scrolling adventure arcade game where the player uses various weapons to eliminate monsters.\n Up, up, down, down, left, right, left, right, B, A, B, A!!! — An anonymous mechanoid

Name: Dazzling Sprint
Desc: An adventure arcade music game. Its unique art style and easy-to-start mechanism make it favored by the young gamers.\nI changed all characters to pretty girls. I'm gonna make a fortune this time! — Teddy

Name: Candy Fortune Bag
Desc: A lucky draw mini-game that purely relies on luck. One could get candies of various flavors.\nCockroach flavor? Wait. Did anyone have it before? — Someone who got weird candies

Name: Plush Fortune Bag
Desc: A lucky draw mini-game that purely relies on luck. One could get various plushes.\nThe reward might seem random to the customer, but not to the boss. — Some fortune bag master

Name: Model Fortune Bag
Desc: A lucky draw mini-game that purely relies on luck. One could get various strange models.\nThis wight. This one must be the legendary limited-edition figurine. — A fanatical collector

Name: Potted Hurricane Lilies
Desc: The signature flower of the Hydrangea Island. It's said to represent the longing for the dead. Where the flowers bloom lies the grave of my old friend who passed away.

Name: Potted Chrysanthemums
Desc: Fragrant flowers that stand aloof from the world.

Name: Potted Hydrangeas
Desc: A potted plant transplanted from the Hydrangea Island. Colorful and gorgeous.

Name: Culture Doodle Board
Desc: Originally a tourist signature wall in the Golden Age. Somehow it has become a colorful graffiti wall.\nDon't report Nanami to anyone! — An anonymous girl

Name: Moonlit Publicity Board
Desc: The sun and the moon rise and set throughout the passage of time.

Name: Misono Publicity Board
Desc: Worship my teacher in the white snow and the light of fireflies.

Name: The Stage
Desc: A stage for various performances and occasionally special performances including mechanoid stage plays and Iaido shows.

Name: Misono Food Stall
Desc: Yata will go to this tile first. A special snack of the Hydrangea Island made from natural ingredients with a pleasant smell.

Name: Claw Machine
Desc: Lucia will go to this tile first. A vintage-style claw machine with various limited-theme Froggie plushes.

Name: Four-wheel Drive Assembly
Desc: Lee will go to this tile first. Pick the parts and assemble a four-wheel drive for a car race within the given time. It tests your hands-on ability.

Name: Piano
Desc: Selena will go to this tile first. The piano in the college's activity room. It's said that the piano would play at midnight, making it one of the "Misono Paranormal Phenomena".

Name: Flower Shop
Desc: Liv will go to this tile first. A flower shop that sells hydrangea souvenirs. Covered by flowers, the shop looks beautiful and elegant.

Name: Norman Hero
Desc: Nanami will go to this tile first. The classic arcade game Norman Hero 4. The player plays as a Norman Mining Corp miner who tries to get rid of the alien pirates.

Name: Movie Poster
Desc: Bianca will go to this tile first. The poster of movie Seven Spearsmen. It's a movie about seven samurai fight against the invader along with the villagers.

Name: Balloon Shooting Stall
Desc: Wanshi will go to this tile first. A two-player balloon shooting mini game. Time to test your shooting skills and collaboration. Absolutely no tampering with the gun!

Name: Suit Store
Desc: Chrome will go to this tile first. Whether you are looking for a suit for a business event or an everyday outfit, you can always find the clothes you want here.
